column7: ('name', 'Casa Brazilian Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', "Casa Restaurant serves Brazilian home cooking from different regions of this vast country. Being a delicious seafood moqueca from Bahia in the northeast or a dish made with organic chicken and okra from the state of Minas Gerais or the national dish of Brazil, the feijoada, a stew of prime meats and black beans with many little dishes on the side. The caipirinha (kai peh ree nha), the national drink of Brazil, comes in the original flavor of lime or in tropical variations such as passion fruit, cashew fruit and coconut. The desserts are all made in house daily and the Brazilian chocolate bonbons, the brigadeiros, are a Brazilian's favorite!")

column7: ('name', 'La Loteria Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', 'Welcome to La Lotería — a new take on authentic Mexican cuisine from Executive Chef/Owner  Julieta Ballesteros (Crema, Los Feliz) and Managing Partner/Owner  Jaime Herrera.  The game La Lotería has been played throughout Mexico since Colonial times. Similar in concept to American Bingo, it is played using 54 widely varied characters and symbols of Mexican culture (like the skull, the moon, the mermaid & the rooster), and it inspires our ambiance, drinks, and menu. Not unlike the game, Mexican cuisine is unique, varied and steeped in tradition. With the cultural touchstone of La Lotería at its core, the restaurant will introduce to New York’s sophisticated palate an exciting and surprising mix of Mexican recipes, ranging from the deliciously elemental “street” taco, to the luscious lobster quesadilla. Come experience the spirit of La Lotería. Our specialty drinks and inspired cuisine await you in our inviting, newly designed West Village space.')

column10:
('description', 'Located in the heart of the West Village, Pinto Garden is home to vibrant and ambitious Thai cuisine prepared with seasonal, locally sourced ingredients. For the menu, Chef Teerawong "Yo" Nanthavatsiri takes inspiration from his favorite dishes found in his home city of Bangkok, as well as throughout Thailand\'s diverse regions.

Chef Yo and his experienced team -- General Manager Kobsak Songyoo, who is also an interior designer for Pinto Restaurant Group -- ensure that Pinto Garden guests will be taken care of and feel nourished as if they are dining at their family\'s house. Our motto is “Eat Well….Be Well."')

column7: ('name', 'Hakata Tonton Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', 'We invite you to try Hakata Tonton’s Authentic Kyushu Japanese Soul Food. We have a number of dishes which may same strange to the eye, but are delicious renditions of the food made famous in Hakata, Japan. Pork, Collagen, and Cod Roe are all specialties of the region and you can enjoy them in various combinations on our Japanese fusion style menu.
Our food is made to share and does not come in any particular order, as is the tradition in Hakata. We invite you to be adventurous and try a number of small plate items so that you get a feeling for our savory cuisine.
We have chosen a number of unique wines and Japanese sake we feel goes well with our savory cuisine and invite you to try a glass or a bottle. We have priced our wines by the bottle way below what most restaurants charge, so you can enjoy without hurting your wallet.
Finally, we invite you to try our collagen cuisine. It’s great for your skin and most importantly, we think you will love our presentation and taste.')

column7: ('name', 'Baby Brasa Organic Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', "BABY BRASA West Village is now serving the best traditional Peruvian dishes in NYC. Responsibly sourced free-range organic chicken and grass fed beef packs in a flavor that can only come from the freshest ingredients and Peruvian spices. Top off your salads, sides, sandwiches  with our premium selection of beer and wine. Also enjoy the full bar and special events like LIVE MUSIC on Saturdays by LA PACHAMAMBO or DJ LINA BRAFORD Friday's of Tropical Disco, follow the instagram for details and upcoming dates.")

column7: ('name', "Murray's Cheese Bar Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable")
column10:
('description', 'We’ve been selling cheese at our Bleecker Street flagship store since 1940, and in 2012 the team behind Murray’s Cheese decided we needed a place to host our friends and neighbors for cheesy brunches, dinners and spirited celebrations. Murray’s Cheese Bar was born, and so was a world of fine cheeses made locally and abroad, selected and arranged by expert mongers or cooked into divine dishes by our seasoned chefs.

We love cheese, but our menu also features seasonal specials, high-quality meat and produce and fantastic happy hour specials during the week. Join us for dinner seven nights a week or weekend brunch next time you’re passing through Greenwich Village and see why we’re so in love with what we serve')

column7: ('name', 'Old Rose Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', "Old Rose is a cafe, restaurant, and bar located on the sunny first floor of The Jane Hotel overlooking the Hudson River. Open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner, the restaurant's menu emphasizes seasonal Italian fare using local produce, and features pizzas and pastas. The beverage menu consists of local craft beers on tap, natural wines, and specialty cocktails.

Reservations are not required but encouraged, though we do reserve ample seating for hotel guests and neighbors.")

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column10:
('description', 'An Ofrenda, in Spanish, is an offering, a gift. At their cozy West Village space, owner Jorge Guzman and Chef Mario Hernandez offer their unique interpretation of classic Mexican cuisine with an innovative cocktail menu of tequila-based drinks.
Named by NYLuxury as “one of the top ten restaurants in New York serving Latin food” and as “Top Tequila Bar in the US” by the editors of USA Today, this intimate and stylish cocina offers its guests a blend of passions. Jorge’s desire is to create a sexy and fun space to enjoy creative cocktails with the best of Latin cuisine. While Chef Mario’s dream is to craft dishes to showcase the indigenous ingredients of Mexico, the foods his ancestors enjoyed, and bring those flavors to a new generation.
This team has joined forces to offer guests a unique dining experience. We look forward to having you.
')

('description', 'Quality Eats is brought to you by the merry band of butchers at Smith & Wollensky and Quality Meats. With an affordable and fun steak-centric menu, Quality Eats is “the future of the New York steakhouse.” (Eater)

column7: ('name', 'The Clam Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', 'The Clam is a 50 seat neighborhood restaurant drawing its inspiration from one of our favorite ingredients, the clam. Mike Price, chef and co-owner, offers a menu that celebrates seasonal, market driven ingredients as well as showcases influences of the Atlantic seaboard. The menu boasts a variety of clam dishes, some classic, some with a new twist and fun originals. The menu is rounded out with iced shellfish, salads, appetizers as well as meat and local seafood entrées. Desserts follow suit, and are inspired by the seasonal and local market offerings. All made in-house, the approach is simple and straightforward with something for everyone. Our shared vision and common goal is to offer genuine hospitality to our guests, garner relationships and establish ourselves not only as a neighborhood gem but also a Greenwich Village destination where our guests can be confident that their experiences are sure to be exceptional.')

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column7: ('name', 'Suprema Provisions Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', "Home of the Top Rated Burger in NYC the Suprema Burger.
Suprema was inspired by the great salumerias of Rome, tapas bars of Barcelona and sidewalk cafes of Paris, Suprema offers a broad selection of pastas, salumi and cheese boards, small plates, and many savory entrées including the the famous Suprema Burger along with a fine wine and cocktail program crafted by renowned sommelier Joshua Wesson.

From truffled deviled eggs to pork shoulder lasagna, Suprema's menu journeys across Europe and America, with a particular emphasis on artisanal cured meat and cheese, and small-production wines, beers and spirits.")

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column7: ('name', 'City Vineyard & Wine Garden at Pier 26 Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', "Offering year round riverfront dining, live music, wine on tap, incredible views, and a one of a kind rooftop bar & lounge, City Vineyard is the latest project by Michael Dorf, founder & CEO of City Winery.
Located on Pier 26 in Hudson River Park, this unique space overlooks the Hudson River and provides the perfect setting to celebrate skilled winemaking and high quality food. Michael's vision of combined dining room, wine garden & event space is delivered by a team of seasoned wine & culinary experts. City Vineyard brings the seasonal bounty of upstate New York to the shores of Manhattan, and our exciting menu is complemented by a carefully curated wine list. City Vineyard offers full-service dining in our main dining room & waterfront wine garden. The Rooftop Bar at City Vineyard offers beer & wine service with incredible views, though does not accept reservations.
Please note, due to unpredictable weather, all reservations are for our indoor main dining room. ")

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column7: ('name', 'Coarse NYC Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', 'Chef Vincent Chirico knows food. Raised in Brooklyn to parents of Italian decent, and having spent part of his childhood in the homeland, Chirico’s early years were peppered with all the cultural advantages of a Mediterranean lifestyle. In those early years, Chirico developed a  reverence for simplicity and a palate fine-tuned to natural flavors. With a love of travel came further developments in the shaping of Chirico’s culinary perspective, including time in Japan where he grew to love local techniques, and preparations from the best kitchens in Paris and other European epicenters of flavor')

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column10:
('description', 'Rahi, (meaning traveler in Hindi) is an artisanal Indian restaurant in Greenwich Village – a collaboration between a young Indian chef with playful artistry, Chintan Pandya, and restaurateur, Roni Mazumdar.

Rahi serves vibrant Indian food, straying from tradition, by adopting the local produce of New York. Guests are taken on a journey through India – each dish with unique traditional flavors. 

White brick walls pulse with the energy of a black and gold mural, painted by famous artists, Yok & Sheryo. Pattern elements represent fragments of memories, a dream sequence, of a woman that travels around India. 

Rahi is designed for indulging the senses over leisurely conversation and enticing plates; for spirited evenings with exotic cocktails.')

column7: ('name', 'Sant Ambroeus - West Village Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', 'Shortly after the original Sant Ambroeus opened its doors in Milan in 1936, a devoted following emerged. This celebrated pasticceria and confetteria became the meeting place for the local intelligentsia, whether beginning their day with Sant Ambroeus’s legendary cappuccino and cornetto, savoring panini at lunch, or spending their evening enjoying refined cuisine in the restaurant’s elegant dining room.
We translated these old-world sensibilities of Sant Ambroeus to modern times, and imported our rich culinary traditions to New York. Each of our restaurants remains authentic to our Milanese origins, and we continue to serve our culturally inspired delectables in a casual yet elegant environment.')

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column10:
('description', "Located in the heart of New York City's West Village, A.O.C. has become a part of the historic and beautiful neighborhood.

Our extensive menu is a collaboration of handed down family recipes from the chef/owner, Romain Bonnans, and classic French fare.

Savor everything from Omelets to Feuille de Brique for brunch. For dinner you might try our Moules Marinieres (a favorite among our customers), a classic Salad Nicoise or a Lobster Risotto, all while enjoying the casual atmosphere. In the summer months, relax in our outdoor garden and experience a little bit of France.")

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column7: ('name', 'While We Were Young Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10: ('description', 'While We Were Young serves healthy, contemporary American cuisine and craft cocktails in a chic and fun setting. Designed after the owners love for surfing, the front bar resembles a wave, the back bar features cutout surfboards in walnut, and the dusty pink banquette references the pink sand beaches of the Bahamas.')

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column10:
('description', "Step beyond our atrium. Agave's serene, smart adobe scene provides a glowing setting for the fusion of tradition and Southwestern innovation of Chef Raul Juarez.
Our menus are created with the greatest care to ensure an enchanted experience. Highlights include our Hand Hacked Avocado Guacamole, seared Ahi tuna tataki tostaditas, and Tejas Blue Crab Quesadillas as well as our delicious entrees such as Fire Grilled Shrimp Tacos with Harvest Corn and Smoked Tomato, Fajitas of Wagyu Kobe Beef Skirt Steak and Chili Cider Glazed Salmon with roasted root vegetables.
Detailed service paired with creative dishes, cocktails and outstanding wines join to create a definitive experience for brunch, lunch and dinner.")

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column7: ('name', 'EN Japanese Brasserie Restaurant - New York, NY | OpenTable')
column10:
('description', 'Experience Japanese dining in a beautiful, authentic Japanese restaurant located in the West Village of Manhattan. We offer the rich traditions of Japanese cooking with Chef Abe Hiroki’s modern yet relaxed style of dining centered around a procession of small plates.


We adhere to the fundamentals of Japanese cooking: respecting the ingredients and their natural flavors, cooking in the moment, and letting the ingredients speak for themselves. We have created an extensive menu, featuring dishes as fresh tofu (prepared six times a night), saikyo miso black cod, stone grilled Washugyu and Wagyu steaks, an assortment of sashimi and sushi rolls and three signature EN Kaiseki tasting menus. To compliment your dining experience, we have developed a list of over 80 sakes and 36 shochus as well as carefully crafted signature cocktails and wine list. Polish your meal off with a choice from 60 Japanese whiskies, a lineup that is hard to beat.')

column6: ('restaurant_images', ['', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''])
column10:
('description', "Roey’s (pronounced ROE-ees) is inspired by old world cafés: spaces where communities come together for nourishment and to share ideas. Roey’s endeavors to bring this sense of community to the West Village by offering an accessible, high quality, nourishing experience in a casual and sophisticated setting. Roey’s seeks to serve its community by offering wholesome and delicious food and beverage all day long, which can be taken to go or enjoyed in the cafe's dining room.


Roey’s is open for breakfast, lunch and dinner as well as weekend brunch and daily happy hour. Roey's accepts takeout and delivery orders.")
